Function Reference/the weekday « WordPress Codex
-----------

Displays the day of the week (e.g. Friday). This tag must be used within
[The Loop](/The_Loop "The Loop").

Replace With
------------

To replace this tag, use
[the\_time()](/Template_Tags/the_time "Template Tags/the time") with
`'l'` as the format string:

    <?php the_time('l'); ?>

See [Formatting Date and
Time](/Formatting_Date_and_Time "Formatting Date and Time") for
information on date and time format string use.

Usage
-----

`  <?php the_weekday() ?> `

Parameters
----------

This tag does not accept any parameters.

Example
-------

     <p>This was posted on a <?php the_weekday() ?>.</p>

Change Log
----------

-   Since: 0.71
-   Replace By:
    [the\_time('l')](/Formatting_Date_and_Time "Formatting Date and Time")

